+// An append-only market-reaction snapshot for a HotEvent (AD-2/AD-5, Story 2.1).
+// The market-reaction module is the sole writer of this table. Each row records
+// ONE market snapshot's TWO signal dimensions — price/volume (priceVolumeTone +
+// priceVolumeValue) and sector/limit-up (sectorLimitUpTone + sectorLimitUpValue
+// + limitUpCount) — plus a tradingSession time context shared by both signals
+// (epic: every signal carries an explicit trading-session time context). Rows are
+// NEVER updated or deleted: every generation appends a new row, so the table is a
+// time series of snapshots for the event (HOT_EVENT ||--o{ REACTION_SNAPSHOT).
+// The public read model projects the LATEST row (createdAt desc, id desc tiebreak)
+// into published_hot_event_reactions; the market-reaction worker V1 only generates
+// the initial snapshot for a published event with no snapshot.
+//
+// FK onDelete: Cascade so a HotEvent deletion cleans up its snapshot history.
+// `source` distinguishes provenance ("template" V1 deterministic fixture-backed
+// derivation; future provider id when a real market-data adapter is wired). V1
+// worker runtime resolves NO adapter → no snapshot is written → prod degrades
+// honestly (AC3); StubMarketDataAdapter is test-only (verify/e2e).
+//
+// NFR: signals are explanatory, never advisory — tone/value describe observed
+// market facts (change percent, sector name, limit-up count) and NEVER contain
+// buy/sell/target-price/position wording.
+//
+// The flat 2-dimension column layout (not a JSON signals array) mirrors V1 AC
+// (exactly two required dimensions) and maps directly to ReactionChip's
+// {tone, value}. Adding a future third dimension (e.g. capital flow) is a
+// schema migration (deferred).
+model MarketReactionSnapshot {
